WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:16.460
Joanna Jimbuku is a nurse. She lives and works in North Australia. Her boss is Bob Mills,

00:16.460 --> 00:26.720
a flying doctor. He and Joanna go everywhere in the Bluebird, Bob's plane. One morning

00:26.720 --> 00:40.640
in August, Joanna answers the phone. "Hello?" she says. "Dr. Mills' office." Then, a baby.

00:40.640 --> 00:53.680
"Yes, I see. And you're in Womara? Okay. We can be there in half an hour." Five minutes

00:53.680 --> 01:06.960
later, Joanna and Bob are in the Bluebird. "How old is this baby?" asks Bob. "Eighteen months,"

01:06.960 --> 01:18.320
says Joanna. After a moment, Bob looks at her. "Womara's near your hometown, isn't it?"

01:18.400 --> 01:29.840
"Yes. That's right." Joanna smiles. "It's a very small place." She looks out of the window.

01:31.440 --> 01:39.120
"There it is," she says. "Can you see between those trees and the river?"

01:39.840 --> 01:49.760
Down on the ground, eight or nine people are waiting for the flying doctor. They take him and Joanna

01:49.760 --> 02:03.600
to a small house. The baby's mother, Jane, is inside it. Bob looks at the little girl for 20 minutes.

02:04.000 --> 02:19.280
Then, he says, "I'm sorry, but Mary is very, very ill. It's her heart. She must go to a hospital in Sydney."

02:20.240 --> 02:36.320
"Sydney?" says Jane. "Yes." Bob puts his hand on the woman's arm. "But it's okay. You can go with her."

02:36.800 --> 02:51.760
Jane looks sad. "How? I've got six other children. I can't just leave them." Suddenly, Joanna has an idea.

02:51.760 --> 03:05.200
"Wait a minute," she says. "Why don't I go to Sydney with Mary? After all, I'm on holiday for two weeks after today."

03:06.160 --> 03:12.400
"Good idea," says the flying doctor. They look at Jane.

03:14.640 --> 03:23.440
"Okay," she says. 24 hours later, Joanna arrives in Sydney for the first time.

03:25.280 --> 03:34.080
Two nurses are waiting at the airport. They drive her and Mary very fast to a big hospital.

03:35.440 --> 03:45.440
Then they take Mary into room 308. A doctor's waiting there.

03:48.000 --> 03:55.840
"Hello," he says. "My name's Paul Griffin." Joanna smiles at him.

03:56.320 --> 04:07.840
"Hello." Then she asks the nurses, "Can I help?" Joanna spends all day at the hospital.

04:09.280 --> 04:15.520
But after eight hours, she's very tired. Paul Griffin sees this.

04:17.920 --> 04:25.040
"Why don't you stay with me and my wife tonight?" he asks. "Thanks,"

04:26.000 --> 04:30.240
says Joanna. "That's really nice of you."

04:33.680 --> 04:37.920
At six o'clock, she and Paul drive to his house.

04:39.920 --> 04:50.000
There, Joanna meets Paul's wife, Fran. She meets their daughter too. Her name is Polly.

04:50.800 --> 04:58.800
After dinner, Paul shows Joanna to her room. Joanna sits on the bed.

05:00.800 --> 05:05.280
"Is Mary going to be okay?" she asks.

05:07.280 --> 05:17.760
"I don't know," Paul replies. Then he says, "but we're going to do everything we can."

05:20.720 --> 05:31.440
After that, Joanna goes to the hospital every day. She helps the nurses and sits beside Mary's bed.

05:33.920 --> 05:43.440
For three days, nothing happens. Then one afternoon, Joanna's reading a book in room 308.

05:44.240 --> 05:55.520
Suddenly, she hears a noise. "What's that?" she thinks. Then she hears it again.

05:59.920 --> 06:11.680
She stands up and walks to Mary's bed. "Mary, it's you. You're sitting up. You're talking."

06:12.640 --> 06:16.720
She runs out of the room and finds Paul.

06:18.320 --> 06:24.640
"Quick, Dr. Griffin," she says. "It's Mary. Come and see."

06:27.040 --> 06:31.760
Later that day, Joanna telephones Bob Mills.

06:33.200 --> 06:38.640
"Yes, that's right. Mary's going to be okay,"

06:39.520 --> 06:45.520
she says with a big smile. "I can bring her home next week."

06:47.280 --> 06:55.520
That evening, the Griffins take Joanna to an expensive restaurant. Joanna sits next to the

06:55.520 --> 07:07.040
window. Outside, she can see the lights of Sydney. "This is beautiful," she says.

07:09.600 --> 07:20.480
Next morning at breakfast, Paul says, "Joanna, you can stay here at home today. After all, Mary's

07:20.480 --> 07:34.720
okay now." "No thanks," says Joanna. "I want to be with her." At the hospital, Paul sees Sister

07:34.720 --> 07:44.880
Clark. "One of my girls is leaving next week and we need someone new," she says.

07:46.960 --> 07:56.720
"What about Joanna Jimbuku? She's a very good nurse. Do you think she wants a job here?"

07:57.600 --> 08:12.720
"Me?" says Joanna that evening. She looks at Paul. "Why not?" he says. "After all, Sister Clark's right.

08:14.080 --> 08:25.200
You're a very good nurse." Joanna is quiet. "Don't say anything now," Paul tells her.

08:26.000 --> 08:39.600
"Just think about it. That's all I'm asking." He walks away, then turns. "But not for too long, okay?"

08:41.200 --> 08:47.760
The next day is Saturday. Joanna goes to the hospital and sees Mary.

08:48.480 --> 09:03.120
"Hello, little one," she says. "You're going home on Monday." Then she thinks, "Or are we going home?"

09:05.760 --> 09:10.560
Two hours later, Fran and Polly meet Joanna for lunch.

09:11.440 --> 09:17.680
"Oh, Joanna. You are going to stay in Sydney, aren't you?"

09:17.680 --> 09:19.920
says Polly.

09:22.400 --> 09:24.800
"I don't know," says Joanna.

09:28.320 --> 09:38.560
Later in the afternoon, Joanna goes for a long walk. The weather is hot. She watches the

09:38.560 --> 09:47.680
people in the streets. She looks at all the shops, cinemas, museums and theaters too.

09:50.320 --> 09:59.280
"Sydney's great," she thinks. "It's very beautiful and there's a lot to see and do."

10:00.240 --> 10:06.880
"But do I really want to live here? That's the question."

10:10.480 --> 10:18.800
Across the street, there's a shop window. Joanna turns and looks in it.

10:19.920 --> 10:26.640
She can see a big painting of some red hills. "Wait a minute,"

10:27.600 --> 10:35.280
she thinks. "I know that place. It's near Womara."

10:38.240 --> 10:41.760
Ten minutes later, a man comes out of the shop.

10:44.320 --> 10:53.120
"Are you okay?" he asks. Joanna smiles. Her eyes are wet.

10:53.440 --> 11:02.880
"Yes," she says. "I'm fine. Really? I'm fine."

11:05.120 --> 11:17.120
Two days later, Bob gets into the Bluebird. Joanna is with him. She waves goodbye to Jane and Mary.

11:17.600 --> 11:23.440
Bob starts the plane and pushes his hat back.

11:25.440 --> 11:36.960
"Listen, thanks for everything, Joanna. This is in Sydney, I mean. It's a beautiful city, isn't it?"

11:39.280 --> 11:46.160
Joanna looks at the red hills of Womara. Then she smiles too.

11:47.120 --> 11:53.920
"Yes," she says. "But it's good to be home."

